which is that there

00:40:29.000 --> 00:40:36.220
was a very significant
dispute between the scientists

00:40:36.220 --> 00:40:38.470
and engineers who were trying
to create the integrated

00:40:38.470 --> 00:40:44.140
system versus the
isolated, siloed systems.

00:40:44.140 --> 00:40:46.300
And that ends up playing
a big role in, I think,

00:40:46.300 --> 00:40:48.467
how many of you perceived
the readings and the kinds

00:40:48.467 --> 00:40:50.320
of questions that you asked.

00:40:50.320 --> 00:40:53.800
I think the place where I'd
like to start our conversation

00:40:53.800 --> 00:40:57.280
is about the mechanisms by which
the computing revolution was

00:40:57.280 --> 00:40:58.390
created.

00:40:58.390 --> 00:41:00.820
We have a question from
Beth, and she poses,

00:41:00.820 --> 00:41:03.130
how much of a
technological revolution

00:41:03.130 --> 00:41:05.920
is the scientific
breakthrough versus the vision

00:41:05.920 --> 00:41:07.940
of how to use it?

00:41:07.940 --> 00:41:10.570
So I think that really
gets at the heart of

00:41:10.570 --> 00:41:14.590
whether or not a technology can
be disruptive or revolutionary

00:41:14.590 --> 00:41:16.600
versus whether the
implementation is

00:41:16.600 --> 00:41:20.328
what actually matters, as you
just noted with Steve Jobs.

00:41:24.167 --> 00:41:26.250
AUDIENCE: Just to clarify,
when you vision, do you

00:41:26.250 --> 00:41:30.390
mean JCR's vision, or do you
mean the visionary who comes

00:41:30.390 --> 00:41:32.865
after, which is Steve Jobs?

00:41:32.865 --> 00:41:34.590
Which vision are
you talking about?

00:41:34.590 --> 00:41:37.530
STEPH: Well, I think
we'll let Beth clarify.

00:41:37.530 --> 00:41:40.320
BETH: I think it is kind
of a cumulative process.

00:41:40.320 --> 00:41:42.760
The reason that Steve Jobs
was able to have a vision

00:41:42.760 --> 00:41:46.080
was because JCR had his vision.

00:41:46.080 --> 00:41:49.470
So it's kind of like at each
step in the road, the reason

00:41:49.470 --> 00:41:51.780
we were able to progress,
was it because of the vision,

00:41:51.780 --> 00:41:54.380
or was it because of
technology, or was it

00:41:54.380 --> 00:41:56.767
this guy was at the right
place at the right time?

00:41:56.767 --> 00:41:58.350
How else could things
have progressed,

00:41:58.350 --> 00:42:01.290
if it had been under
different circumstance?

00:42:04.842 --> 00:42:06.300
STEPH: So how much
weight, I guess,

00:42:06.300 --> 00:42:09.480
are we giving the invention,
the mechanism by which this

00:42:09.480 --> 00:42:11.111
