01:06:43.623 --> 01:06:45.790
that operates at both the
personal and institutional

01:06:45.790 --> 01:06:46.980
levels, as we talked about.

01:06:46.980 --> 01:06:49.565
And then secondly, DARPA's
organizational rule set.

01:06:52.180 --> 01:06:58.050
DARPA also creates lots of
the foundational technologies

01:06:58.050 --> 01:07:02.480
behind what is called the
revolution in military affairs.

01:07:02.480 --> 01:07:04.155
So here's the setting.

01:07:07.410 --> 01:07:11.910
Harold Brown And Bill Perry are
running Jimmy Carter's Defense

01:07:11.910 --> 01:07:12.440
Department.

01:07:12.440 --> 01:07:14.090
So Harold Brown's
Secretary of Defense.

01:07:14.090 --> 01:07:15.173
He's president of Caltech.

01:07:17.370 --> 01:07:19.980
And Perry is out of Stanford.

01:07:19.980 --> 01:07:21.930
They are great technologists.

01:07:21.930 --> 01:07:25.110
Imagine the top leadership
of the Defense Department

01:07:25.110 --> 01:07:28.170
and the hands of really
hot-shot technologists.

01:07:28.170 --> 01:07:30.970
Doesn't usually happen.

01:07:30.970 --> 01:07:32.940
And they've got a big
problem on their hands.

01:07:32.940 --> 01:07:37.170
The problem is the American
army, in particular,

01:07:37.170 --> 01:07:39.840
has been completely
demoralized by the Vietnam War,

01:07:39.840 --> 01:07:42.360
and has largely disintegrated.

01:07:42.360 --> 01:07:47.340
It is not, in many ways,
a truly functioning force.

01:07:47.340 --> 01:07:50.010
And the Cold War is
heating up, and there's

01:07:50.010 --> 01:07:53.970
a monster presence of
Soviet and Allied armies

01:07:53.970 --> 01:07:55.410
in Eastern Europe.

01:07:55.410 --> 01:07:58.860
And the problem that
Brown and Perry have got

01:07:58.860 --> 01:08:02.730
is that, because the US Army
is weak and perceived as weak,

01:08:02.730 --> 01:08:07.860
there's kind of nothing in the
way of that Soviet army having

01:08:07.860 --> 01:08:12.060
the capability of moving
right into Western Europe.

01:08:12.060 --> 01:08:17.080
And that's not a good
situation because then you

01:08:17.080 --> 01:08:22.130
have to decide whether to use
nuclear weapons very quickly.

01:08:22.130 --> 01:08:23.410
You don't have a lot of time.

01:08:23.410 --> 01:08:24.910
You've got to decide
whether you use

01:08:24.910 --> 01:08:26.890
nuclear weapons,
which essentially

01:08:26.890 --> 01:08:29.290
means ending the world.

01:08:29.290 --> 01:08:32.770
It's not the kind of decision
you want to have to make.

01:08:32.770 --> 01:08:38.330
So Perry and Brown started
thinking about what

01:08:38.330 --> 01:08:40.130
they call an offset strategy.

01:08:40.130 --> 01:08:43.850
Can we start to
restore the strength

01:08:43.850 --> 01:08:45.649
of the American military?

01:08:45.649 --> 01:08:49.160
They're not going to do it
with a mass army, and a citizen

01:08:49.160 --> 01:08:54.680
army, and building
thousands of tanks,

01:08:54.680 --> 01:08:57.950
and adding millions
to the military.

01:08:57.950 --> 01:09:00.140
That's unaffordable
and they're just not--

01:09:00.140 --> 01:09:02.180
it's not going to happen.

01:09:02.180 --> 01:09:03.740
And they'd be
putting those people

01:09:03.740 --> 01:09:05.870
into a broken
institution anyway.

01:09:05.870 --> 01:09:08.021
So the Army's in the
process of restoring itself

01:09:08.021 --> 01:09:09.979
through leadership of
people like Colin Powell,

01:09:09.979 --> 01:09:13.160
and a whole generation
of new army leaders

01:09:13.160 --> 01:09:15.500
that really restore
that operation

01:09:15.500 --> 01:09:17.600
in a remarkable kind of way.

01:09:17.600 --> 01:09:18.740
It restores itself.

01:09:18.740 --> 01:09:22.760
But that is an underway
project at that time.

01:09:22.760 --> 01:09:27.020
And what Perry and Brown
start is a whole set

01:09:27.020 --> 01:09:31.220
of thinking about can we get
a significant on-the-ground

01:09:31.220 --> 01:09:35.810
conventional warfare superiority
so that the Soviet Union won't

01:09:35.810 --> 01:09:39.470
even think about coming
through the Fulda Gap

01:09:39.470 --> 01:09:41.990
and moving on Western Europe.

01:09:41.990 --> 01:09:47.330
And that's what they embark on,
and that becomes DARPA's job.

01:09:47.330 --> 01:09:56.060
So DARPA develops precision
strike, they develop stealth,

01:09:56.060 --> 01:09:59.090
and they develop UAVs
or drones as core.

01:09:59.090 --> 01:10:02.030
And then they're also doing a
lot of stuff with submarines

01:10:02.030 --> 01:10:03.380
that nobody ever talks about.

01:10:03.380 --> 01:10:05.150
So I don't know what that is.

01:10:05.150 --> 01:10:08.510
Something's going on there with
submarines, undersea warfare.

01:10:08.510 --> 01:10:10.170
But we know about
the other three.

01:10:10.170 --> 01:10:12.530
We have a pretty good
idea what those look like.

01:10:12.530 --> 01:10:20.690
And these are not technologies
that the services want.

01:10:20.690 --> 01:10:23.180
The Air Force is
dominated by pilots.

01:10:23.180 --> 01:10:25.160
They don't want drones.

01:10:25.160 --> 01:10:27.970
That's like the last
thing they want.

01:10:27.970 --> 01:10:31.150
The Air Force wants airplanes
that can actually fly.

01:10:31.150 --> 01:10:33.340
They don't want
these stealth things

01:10:33.340 --> 01:10:36.742
that, if the computers
weren't continually adjusting

01:10:36.742 --> 01:10:38.200
the exact movement
of the aircraft,

01:10:38.200 --> 01:10:40.030
it would fall like a rock.

01:10:40.030 --> 01:10:41.440
It's completely maneuverable.

01:10:41.440 --> 01:10:43.740
It's like flying a bus.

01:10:43.740 --> 01:10:44.965
No, really.

01:10:44.965 --> 01:10:46.090
These are not maneuverable.

01:10:46.090 --> 01:10:48.940
Nobody can see them,
but it's still a bus.

01:10:48.940 --> 01:10:52.420
So the Air Force
doesn't want this thing.

01:10:52.420 --> 01:10:55.480
But DARPA, in the
case of stealth,

01:10:55.480 --> 01:10:58.270
working with Lockheed--
which does some fascinating

01:10:58.270 --> 01:11:01.150
translation of actually
Russian scientific literature

01:11:01.150 --> 01:11:02.830
and develops the
concept of stealth--

01:11:02.830 --> 01:11:07.450
and then DARPA jumps on it with
Lockheed and his Skunk Works--

01:11:07.450 --> 01:11:10.900
works on developing stealth.

01:11:10.900 --> 01:11:13.750
It's working on
precision strike.

01:11:13.750 --> 01:11:15.430
Completely changes warfare.

01:11:15.430 --> 01:11:18.400
Completely changes warfare.

01:11:18.400 --> 01:11:20.980
In the Gulf War--

01:11:20.980 --> 01:11:23.862
which was where all this stuff
got shown and demonstrated,

01:11:23.862 --> 01:11:26.320
and that's where this phrase
revolution in military affairs

01:11:26.320 --> 01:11:27.220
comes from--

01:11:27.220 --> 01:11:28.720
the Russians saw this stuff.

01:11:28.720 --> 01:11:30.670
Revolution in military
affairs is their term

01:11:30.670 --> 01:11:33.370
for what we pulled off.

01:11:33.370 --> 01:11:37.540
They were stunned that
these technologies created

01:11:37.540 --> 01:11:41.020
a whole new kind of capability
on the ground for the US

01:11:41.020 --> 01:11:42.133
military that was just--

01:11:42.133 --> 01:11:43.300
they had no defense against.

01:11:43.300 --> 01:11:47.560
We were essentially up against
a Soviet-trained and style army

01:11:47.560 --> 01:11:51.310
in the Gulf War in Iraq,
and their air defense system

01:11:51.310 --> 01:11:53.865
fell apart in a very
short period of time.

01:11:53.865 --> 01:11:55.240
They could not
deal with stealth.

01:11:55.240 --> 01:11:57.640
They could not deal with drones.

01:11:57.640 --> 01:12:00.820
This continuous battlefield
awareness, the airline battle

01:12:00.820 --> 01:12:03.460
doctrine that was enabled by
these different technologies

01:12:03.460 --> 01:12:07.360
created an entirely different
kind of military force.

01:12:07.360 --> 01:12:10.510
So DARPA's doing this
stuff, but this stuff

01:12:10.510 --> 01:12:13.667
gets stood up
within the military.

01:12:13.667 --> 01:12:15.750
It's hard to think what
the civilian application--

01:12:15.750 --> 01:12:18.520
we're now working away
in civilian applications

01:12:18.520 --> 01:12:20.830
on drones, so that's
transferring over.

01:12:20.830 --> 01:12:22.790
That could be
pretty interesting.

01:12:22.790 --> 01:12:24.790
It's already starting
to get interesting.

01:12:24.790 --> 01:12:27.070
GPS is another part of
that story that's already

01:12:27.070 --> 01:12:30.580
long since transferred
over, that DARPA

01:12:30.580 --> 01:12:33.910
works on helping to nurture.

01:12:33.910 --> 01:12:38.260
Maybe stealth will
transfer over,

01:12:38.260 --> 01:12:43.510
because if we do something
resembling autonomous vehicles,

01:12:43.510 --> 01:12:47.710
you really want inverse stealth
so that the radar systems can

01:12:47.710 --> 01:12:49.690
really see your vehicle,
that they're not

01:12:49.690 --> 01:12:53.200
going to miss you in the noise.

01:12:53.200 --> 01:12:57.130
Cars could look a lot weirder
if they go stealth, but--

01:12:57.130 --> 01:12:58.720
inverse stealth,
but that may be what

01:12:58.720 --> 01:13:01.540
we need to do in order to
make these autonomous vehicle

01:13:01.540 --> 01:13:03.427
systems really operable.

