abstract question,

01:24:16.535 --> 01:24:18.910
but follows along with this
idea of creating these change

01:24:18.910 --> 01:24:19.740
agents.

01:24:19.740 --> 01:24:23.530
And so somebody asked, is there
this sense that these change

01:24:23.530 --> 01:24:26.050
agents, like the ones
that are found in DARPA--

01:24:26.050 --> 01:24:27.760
is it important to
create these change

01:24:27.760 --> 01:24:33.070
agents by giving you a whole
bunch of money and letting do

01:24:33.070 --> 01:24:35.020
you do--

01:24:35.020 --> 01:24:36.950
use your own discretion,
as product managers,

01:24:36.950 --> 01:24:39.970
to figure out what you
want to do, or to find

01:24:39.970 --> 01:24:43.667
these people that are
doing these fringe research

01:24:43.667 --> 01:24:45.250
opportunities that
might be high risk,

01:24:45.250 --> 01:24:47.750
and they might not just have
the funding, and go from there?

01:24:47.750 --> 01:24:50.830
And so it's the do you
want to create these change

01:24:50.830 --> 01:24:52.990
agents by giving
it to the people

01:24:52.990 --> 01:24:55.990
that you think are capable, or
do you want to go out and find

01:24:55.990 --> 01:25:00.730
these people who may not be
proven in their field yet,

01:25:00.730 --> 01:25:04.853
or might not have research
that is still at this high risk

01:25:04.853 --> 01:25:05.353
phase?

01:25:08.180 --> 01:25:10.300
STEPH: Could I ask
clarifying question?

01:25:10.300 --> 01:25:11.980
Do you mean in the
context of DARPA,

01:25:11.980 --> 01:25:15.370
