[INAUDIBLE] fields

01:30:37.670 --> 01:30:40.600
and new areas, it might easier,
and so it's easier to form.

01:30:40.600 --> 01:30:45.660
But I think for energy, how
do you make that distinction?

01:30:45.660 --> 01:30:47.992
Because I feel
other legacy sectors

01:30:47.992 --> 01:30:49.863
would be a lot
harder to come in.

01:30:49.863 --> 01:30:51.530
WILLIAM BONVILLIAN:
Well, the military's

01:30:51.530 --> 01:30:53.180
a hard legacy sector,
because remember,

01:30:53.180 --> 01:30:54.800
the services have the money.

01:30:54.800 --> 01:30:56.750
They have their
procurement budgets.

01:30:56.750 --> 01:30:59.330
And if they don't want to
do it, it's really hard

01:30:59.330 --> 01:31:00.210
to get them to do it.

01:31:00.210 --> 01:31:03.620
So that's why that island-bridge
model's so crucial for DARPA

01:31:03.620 --> 01:31:06.020
being able to rely on
the Secretary of Defense

01:31:06.020 --> 01:31:08.580
to kind of override
some of the directions

01:31:08.580 --> 01:31:09.830
where the services want to go.

01:31:09.830 --> 01:31:14.900
It's still not easy, but all of
these three technology areas--

01:31:14.900 --> 01:31:17.420
position strike,
UAVs, and stealth--

01:31:17.420 --> 01:31:20.930
were all stood up despite some
pretty significant service

01:31:20.930 --> 01:31:22.250
opposition.

01:31:22.250 --> 01:31:25.220
Not uniformly-- different
parts of the services

01:31:25.220 --> 01:31:27.980
saw what the possibilities were,
so I want to make that uniform.

01:31:27.980 --> 01:31:29.600
But it was still tough.

01:31:29.600 --> 01:31:31.950
These were not
easy to implement.

